A vintage 1960s technical illustration style image showing a complex mechanical filing cabinet that has been opened to reveal an intricate clockwork mechanism inside. The cabinet drawers contain neatly organized rows of punch cards and paper documents, while brass gears, cogs, and pneumatic tubes connect different compartments, transforming raw paper into glowing crystalline data structures. Warm sepia and amber tones dominate, with touches of teal and copper. The scene has a cross-section view like an old encyclopedia diagram, showing both the exterior wooden cabinet and the fantastical inner workings. Dust motes float in shafts of light from a nearby window, suggesting a professor's study or inventor's workshop.
